  "texts": [
    "A crucial question is how to facilitate an explanatory interaction in real-time in which explanations are recomputed or adapted in reaction to users' signalling of understanding, doubts, uncertainty, etc.",
    "A balance needs to be found between quickly providing pre-computed answers for certain standard information needs and computing highly adapted and contextualized, but more time-intensive answers.",
    "While the first approach might be fast, it might lack contextual adequacy and suitability.",
    "The second approach might be slower but yield highly relevant and contextually adequate explanations.",
    "Finding a balance between both approaches to ensure a real-time interaction seems an important avenue for future work."
  ],
